Column one
All about Southern Breeze in Fort Myers
Thrive in the Florida Sunshine
Your dollar goes further in Florida – there’s NO state income tax here! Fort Myers has everything you want, including small town friendliness and the convenience of big city services. When your new address is at quiet, secluded Southern Breeze RV & MHC, you’ll be able to find all the things you need at these nearby locations.
Column one
Publix Supermarket at The Shops at Village Walk
Supermarket with fresh meats, veggies, prepared foods, bakery, adult beverages, pet foods, cleaning supplies, and everything you expect from a major supermarket.
Learn more +
Walmart Supercenter in Fort Myers
Department store with groceries, auto service center, vision care, pharmacy, and everything else.  6am – 11pm.
Learn more +
Edison Mall
Anchored by Dillard’s and JC Penney, Edison Mall in Fort Myers offers dozens of stores, special events, and acres of free parking!
Learn more +
Column one
Healthcare
Your family and pets are never far from quality medical care in Fort Myers.
Lee Memorial Hospital
– For more than 100 years, Lee Health has offered a full range of outpatient and inpatient services, emergency care, general acute care, and surgical services. Open 24 hours.
Learn more +
Lee County VA Clinic
– A handicapped-accessible VA outpatient clinic in nearby Cape Coral with general medical care, pharmacy, and mental health services.
Learn more +
Edison Park Animal Hospital
– Chosen as a ‘Neighborhood Favorite’ every year since 2019, Edison Park Animal Hospital offers exams, consultations, vaccinations, surgery, nutritional counseling, microchipping, a pharmacy, and more! New clients are welcome!
Learn more +
